{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 17:21:12.575866", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission successful.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"server_access_router\", \"router_core_1\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"ospf_area_misconfiguration\", \"host_incorrect_ip\"]\n\nNotes:\n- server_access_router is localized as the device injecting the server subnet (10.200.0.0/24) into OSPF without segmentation/ACLs, allowing hosts direct access to backend servers — design/control missing.\n- router_core_1 has an OSPF router-id misconfiguration (172.16.0.0) — configuration error that should be corrected.\n\nIf you want, I can now produce specific remediation steps (commands/config snippets) to:\n- Stop advertising 10.200.0.0/24 into OSPF or apply route filters/VRF/ACL to prevent host access to backend servers, and\n- Correct the router-id on router_core_1 and verify OSPF neighbor/LSDB health.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 3102, "output_tokens": 206, "total_tokens": 3308, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
